Great options for vegetarians and I have no complaints about the food (when we did get what we ordered). But I cannot say the same for service. The people behind the counter must have been sleepy or high because they messed up our order twice. 2 people in our group didn't get the sandwiches they ordered and the salad was disappointing to say the least.

My husband and I were in the DC area recently and went here for a late lunch. I can't tell you how great an experience it was for us.  We were hot, tired, and a hop from cranky when we got here.  That completely changed for us.  The servers were personable, friendly, accurate in their answers and just down right nice.  The food was fantastic.  Simple with a well done flair.  Great soup, sandwich, and salad. Not to mention cookies. I almost never give reviews but this place and these people deserve the best I can give. If you guys are reading this Thank You so much from the woman who told you that you had turned her day around. You really did.
